The Super Falcons of Nigeria defeated Slovakia 4-3 in their second game of the Cyprus Women’s Cup on Friday. Anam Imoh scored a late minute goal that made Nigeria defeat Slovakia. The Head Coach, Thomas Dennerby, made seven changes in the team that lost 4-1 in their first match against Austria on Wednesday.
Skipper, Rita Chikwelu scored twice, Defender Osinachi Ohale also scored to give Nigeria 3-nil lead in the first half.
The second stanza was different as Slovakia rallied back to level scores 3-3, but a late goal by substitute Anam Imo became the winning goal for Nigeria’s Super Falcons.
